# Python Standards

## Style
- Type hints for function signatures
- Dataclasses for config objects (see `scripts/utils/imaging.py`)
- `np.random.default_rng(seed)` not `np.random.seed()`

## Data Pipeline Pattern
```python
# Scripts use argparse, print progress, save metadata JSON
def main():
    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='...')
    # ... args
    # Print banner with params
    # Process with progress logging
    # Save metadata.json alongside outputs
```

## Dataset Class Pattern
- GT path derived from input path: `train_wf/` → `train_gt/`, `/wf/` → `/gt/`
- Never use `str.replace('wf', 'gt')` on full paths (breaks `wf2density`)
- Use explicit path construction instead

## Pandas Compatibility
- Don't use `df[col].values[:] = 0` (read-only in newer pandas)
- Use dict-based tracking instead of DataFrame for metrics (see `LogTracker`)
